  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6599 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-33.4B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+45.6B), dealers are currently in neutral hedging mode but positioned to sell any push toward 6605 and aggressively buy any dip toward 6590. The recent regime flip into PIN with massive GEX surge (599% in 5min) creates a tight trading range where dealers will actively dampen volatility through mean-reversion flows. Key inflection points are the 6590 support wall where dealer buying accelerates and 6605 resistance where dealer selling kicks in, with the 6621 flip level acting as the broader regime boundary.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to ping-pong between 6590-6605 as dealers fight any directional moves.",
